    {
      "Text": "Security update for multipath-tools",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for multipath-tools fixes the following issues:\n\nUpdate to version 0.9.8+292+suse.c0523c1.\n\n- kpartx: integer overflow in the GPT partition table size calculation can lead to heap OOB read via crafted USB device\n  or disk image(bsc#1268145).\n- kpartx: missing bounds check can lead to a DASD VOL1 unbounded array write via a crafted DASD disk with more than 256\n  consecutive format labels (bsc#1268144).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
